00:42:21.190 --> 00:42:21.940 align:middle line:90%
Is that what you're saying?

00:42:21.940 --> 00:42:22.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:42:22.740 --> 00:42:26.490 align:middle line:84%
I began to see it was not only
east to west, north to south.

00:42:26.490 --> 00:42:27.420 align:middle line:90%
It was up and down.

00:42:27.420 --> 00:42:30.140 align:middle line:90%


00:42:30.140 --> 00:42:32.080 align:middle line:84%
I found that there
was some reason why

00:42:32.080 --> 00:42:34.540 align:middle line:84%
they were marking the
mountains with elevations

00:42:34.540 --> 00:42:35.440 align:middle line:90%
that fit the system.

00:42:35.440 --> 00:42:38.160 align:middle line:90%


00:42:38.160 --> 00:42:41.890 align:middle line:84%
When they draw a line,
