00:43:29.930 --> 00:43:31.280 align:middle line:90%
You can find it in Stonehenge.

00:43:31.280 --> 00:43:33.570 align:middle line:84%
You can find it in
Tiwanaku, Bolivia.

00:43:33.570 --> 00:43:34.864 align:middle line:90%
You can find it--

00:43:34.864 --> 00:43:35.780 align:middle line:90%
>> All over the world.

00:43:35.780 --> 00:43:37.910 align:middle line:90%
>> All over the world.

00:43:37.910 --> 00:43:39.960 align:middle line:84%
>> This would then
suggest a common source.

00:43:39.960 --> 00:43:40.825 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:43:40.825 --> 00:43:50.050 align:middle line:90%


00:43:50.050 --> 00:43:53.320 align:middle line:84%
>> To get closer to
that mysterious source,

00:43:53.320 --> 00:43:56.350 align:middle line:84%
we need to go to the oldest
civilization in Mexico,

00:43:56.350 --> 00:43:57.330 align:middle line:90%
at La Venta.

00:43:57.330 --> 00:44:02.840 align:middle line:90%


00:44:02.840 --> 00:44:05.220 align:middle line:84%
Excavations along
the Gulf of Mexico

00:44:05.220 --> 00:44:08.180 align:middle line:84%
have revealed traces of
people whose works of art

00:44:08.180 --> 00:44:10.250 align:middle line:84%
contradict all
established theories

00:44:10.250 --> 00:44:13.490 align:middle line:84%
about the growth of
civilization in the Americas.

00:44:13.490 --> 00:44:19.700 align:middle line:90%
They flourished 3,500 years ago.

00:44:19.700 --> 00:44:22.070 align:middle line:84%
Archaeologists call
them the Olmecs.

00:44:22.070 --> 00:44:24.331 align:middle line:84%
We don't know what
they called themselves.

00:44:24.331 --> 00:44:26.920 align:middle line:90%


00:44:26.920 --> 00:44:28.420 align:middle line:84%
All that's certain
is that they were

00:44:28.420 --> 00:44:31.000 align:middle line:84%
a high civilization
with their own writing

00:44:31.000 --> 00:44:33.120 align:middle line:90%
that hasn't yet been deciphered.

00:44:33.120 --> 00:44:36.340 align:middle line:84%
And that they were a
civilization of sky watchers.

00:44:36.340 --> 00:44:37.730 align:middle line:90%
A civilization of astronomers.

00:44:37.730 --> 00:44:39.986 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:44:39.986 --> 00:44:45.680 align:middle line:90%


00:44:45.680 --> 00:44:47.780 align:middle line:84%
The principal Olmec
make site at La Venta

00:44:47.780 --> 00:44:50.030 align:middle line:84%
was dominated by two
astronomically-aligned

00:44:50.030 --> 00:44:50.830 align:middle line:90%
pyramids.

00:44:50.830 --> 00:44:54.070 align:middle line:90%


00:44:54.070 --> 00:44:57.770 align:middle line:84%
The site was demolished by
the oil industry in the 1950s,

00:44:57.770 --> 00:45:00.110 align:middle line:84%
but archaeologists were
at least able to rescue

00:45:00.110 --> 00:45:01.522 align:middle line:90%
its extraordinary sculptures.

00:45:01.522 --> 00:45:09.250 align:middle line:90%


00:45:09.250 --> 00:45:11.935 align:middle line:84%
So far, nearly 20 of them
have been discovered that Le

00:45:11.935 --> 00:45:13.610 align:middle line:90%
Venta and other Olmec sites.

00:45:13.610 --> 00:45:17.230 align:middle line:90%


00:45:17.230 --> 00:45:18.930 align:middle line:90%
Some weigh up to 60 tons.

00:45:18.930 --> 00:45:21.550 align:middle line:90%


00:45:21.550 --> 00:45:24.470 align:middle line:84%
All represent people with
extremely distinctive features.

00:45:24.470 --> 00:45:29.120 align:middle line:90%


00:45:29.120 --> 00:45:33.110 align:middle line:84%
Because of an unpleasant
mixture of political correctness

00:45:33.110 --> 00:45:36.410 align:middle line:84%
and academic dogma,
scholars have never

00:45:36.410 --> 00:45:38.750 align:middle line:84%
really wanted to get
to grips with the heart

00:45:38.750 --> 00:45:40.870 align:middle line:90%
of the Olmec enigma.

00:45:40.870 --> 00:45:45.140 align:middle line:84%
The dogma is that the Americas
were peopled purely and simply

00:45:45.140 --> 00:45:47.840 align:middle line:84%
by Asiatics who
crossed the Bering

00:45:47.840 --> 00:45:53.300 align:middle line:84%
Strait when it was a land
bridge during the last ice age.

00:45:53.300 --> 00:45:57.950 align:middle line:84%
The problem is that the stone
faces left behind by the Olmecs

00:45:57.950 --> 00:46:00.490 align:middle line:90%
aren't the faces of Asiatics.

00:46:00.490 --> 00:46:02.030 align:middle line:84%
On the contrary,
they show us people

00:46:02.030 --> 00:46:07.340 align:middle line:84%
who are clearly and unmistakably
proud and charismatic Africans.

00:46:07.340 --> 00:46:11.480 align:middle line:84%
And other people who are
clearly and unmistakably bearded

00:46:11.480 --> 00:46:14.860 align:middle line:90%
Caucasians.

00:46:14.860 --> 00:46:19.090 align:middle line:84%
The mix of races portrayed here
raises fundamental questions

00:46:19.090 --> 00:46:22.330 align:middle line:84%
about the prehistory
of the Americas.

00:46:22.330 --> 00:46:24.550 align:middle line:84%
Who were these
conspicuous strangers

00:46:24.550 --> 00:46:26.870 align:middle line:84%
who visited the New
World thousands of years

00:46:26.870 --> 00:46:27.670 align:middle line:90%
before Columbus?

00:46:27.670 --> 00:46:31.860 align:middle line:90%


00:46:31.860 --> 00:46:34.740 align:middle line:84%
Mexico abounds with
myths of bearded gods

00:46:34.740 --> 00:46:37.890 align:middle line:84%
who came from across the
sea after a great flood,

00:46:37.890 --> 00:46:42.600 align:middle line:84%
in boats that moved by
themselves without paddles.

00:46:42.600 --> 00:46:44.550 align:middle line:84%
One of the mysteries
of these traditions

00:46:44.550 --> 00:46:46.830 align:middle line:84%
is that the bearded
gods are always

00:46:46.830 --> 00:46:49.020 align:middle line:90%
associated with serpents.

00:46:49.020 --> 00:46:51.655 align:middle line:84%
And that these serpents are
always depicted with plumes.

00:46:51.655 --> 00:46:53.960 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:46:53.960 --> 00:46:55.940 align:middle line:90%


00:46:55.940 --> 00:46:59.164 align:middle line:90%
Feathered serpents.

00:46:59.164 --> 00:47:01.600 align:middle line:84%
We saw a representation
of the feathered serpent

00:47:01.600 --> 00:47:02.980 align:middle line:90%
at Teotihuacan.

00:47:02.980 --> 00:47:06.990 align:middle line:90%
His image is all over the site.

00:47:06.990 --> 00:47:09.201 align:middle line:84%
And we saw him at
Chichen Itza, his form

00:47:09.201 --> 00:47:10.450 align:middle line:90%
coming to life on the equinox.

00:47:10.450 --> 00:47:15.050 align:middle line:90%


00:47:15.050 --> 00:47:17.850 align:middle line:84%
The feathered serpent
was the legendary bringer

00:47:17.850 --> 00:47:20.790 align:middle line:84%
of civilization to Central
America, the teacher

00:47:20.790 --> 00:47:23.380 align:middle line:90%
of astronomy and architecture.

00:47:23.380 --> 00:47:28.230 align:middle line:90%


00:47:28.230 --> 00:47:31.380 align:middle line:84%
But the oldest image of him
we know about is at La Venta.

00:47:31.380 --> 00:47:36.280 align:middle line:90%


00:47:36.280 --> 00:47:44.250 align:middle line:84%
This piece dates back
to at least 1,500 BC.

00:47:44.250 --> 00:47:47.430 align:middle line:84%
The feathered serpent was
the symbol not only of a god,

00:47:47.430 --> 00:47:50.910 align:middle line:90%
but of a group of human beings.

00:47:50.910 --> 00:47:53.460 align:middle line:84%
Mayan sacred texts
call them plumed

00:47:53.460 --> 00:47:58.790 align:middle line:84%
serpents-- great knowers, great
thinkers in their very being.

00:47:58.790 --> 00:48:02.190 align:middle line:84%
To the Aztecs, they were
light-skinned and bearded.

00:48:02.190 --> 00:48:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And were said to have
reached the shores of Mexico

00:48:04.570 --> 00:48:06.380 align:middle line:84%
in boats that moved
without paddles.

00:48:06.380 --> 00:48:08.760 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:48:08.760 --> 00:48:13.530 align:middle line:90%


00:48:13.530 --> 00:48:15.870 align:middle line:84%
What makes me certain
I'm on to something

00:48:15.870 --> 00:48:18.060 align:middle line:84%
is that serpent
symbolism is found

00:48:18.060 --> 00:48:21.520 align:middle line:90%
all across the ancient world.

00:48:21.520 --> 00:48:24.240 align:middle line:84%
In the temples of
Angkor in Cambodia,

00:48:24.240 --> 00:48:28.075 align:middle line:84%
images of gigantic serpents
with many heads are everywhere.

00:48:28.075 --> 00:48:38.785 align:middle line:90%


00:48:38.785 --> 00:48:43.450 align:middle line:84%
And far away in Egypt, in
the Valley of the Kings,

00:48:43.450 --> 00:48:45.870 align:middle line:84%
there's a representation
of a human soul

00:48:45.870 --> 00:48:47.326 align:middle line:90%
resting on a feathered serpent.

00:48:47.326 --> 00:48:56.750 align:middle line:90%


00:48:56.750 --> 00:48:58.640 align:middle line:10%
I think the
similarities are just

00:48:58.640 --> 00:49:02.950 align:middle line:10%
too great to be passed
off as coincidence,

00:49:02.950 --> 00:49:06.240 align:middle line:10%
but experts insist there was no
contact between these cultures.

00:49:06.240 --> 00:49:10.040 align:middle line:90%


00:49:10.040 --> 00:49:12.060 align:middle line:84%
But if there was
no contact, then

00:49:12.060 --> 00:49:14.910 align:middle line:84%
how do we explain the shared
symbolism and beliefs?

00:49:14.910 --> 00:49:19.240 align:middle line:90%


00:49:19.240 --> 00:49:23.710 align:middle line:84%
I think the only explanation
is an earlier lost civilization

00:49:23.710 --> 00:49:27.280 align:middle line:84%
that influenced them both,
far back in prehistory.

00:49:27.280 --> 00:49:37.620 align:middle line:90%


00:49:37.620 --> 00:49:40.650 align:middle line:84%
It was a civilization
of seafarers, who

00:49:40.650 --> 00:49:42.150 align:middle line:90%
had explored the entire globe.

00:49:42.150 --> 00:49:48.710 align:middle line:90%


00:49:48.710 --> 00:49:51.190 align:middle line:10%
The enigmatic and
unexplained statues

00:49:51.190 --> 00:49:55.210 align:middle line:10%
on Easter Island marooned
in the middle of the Pacific

00:49:55.210 --> 00:49:57.770 align:middle line:10%
may provide the key.

00:49:57.770 --> 00:50:36.438 align:middle line:90%